of matrix model and gauge theory results.




Integrating-Out All Flavors 

In this section we compute the gauge theory effective superpotential
at its critical points. The unbroken symmetries determine its value up to an unknown function of one variable. By requiring consistency with
the high energy theory, we
construct a differential equation for this function. We first solve
it for the special case of an  theory with three flavors and then turn to the general
case.


